[Cover system on a basis]
  \label{def:basis_cov_system}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.BasisCovSystem}
  \uses{def:cech_complex}
  \textit{Project-bespoke encoding of conditions (1)--(2) of Stacks 01EO.}
  A \emph{cover system on a basis} for a scheme \(X\) is the lightweight record consisting of:
  a basis \(\mathcal{B} \subseteq \mathrm{Opens}(X)\) for the topology; a set \(\mathrm{Cov}\) of
  admissible open coverings; the \emph{faces-in-basis} datum that for every covering
  \(\mathcal{U} : U = \bigcup_{i} U_i\) in \(\mathrm{Cov}\) one has \(U \in \mathcal{B}\) and every
  finite intersection \(U_{i_0 \ldots i_p} \in \mathcal{B}\) (condition (1)); and the
  \emph{cofinality} datum that for every \(V \in \mathcal{B}\) the coverings of \(V\) lying in
  \(\mathrm{Cov}\) are cofinal among all open coverings of \(V\) (condition (2)). It carries no
  colimit or derived-functor machinery: it records exactly the combinatorial data that conditions
  (1)--(2) of Lemma~\ref{lem:cech_to_cohomology_on_basis} demand. The cofinality datum is stated in
  precisely the shape consumed by Lemma~\ref{lem:ses_cech_h1}.
\end{definition}

